#CHIP YM2151
#CLOCK 3579545

; YM2151 Pitch Bend Test — Testing portamento and frequency modulation
;
; Tests the YM2151's pitch bend capabilities by:
; 1. Starting on a note and bending up
; 2. Bending down
; 3. Wide frequency sweep
; 4. Rapid frequency modulation
;
; This validates the KCI (Keyboard Code Index) and frequency register
; handling under pitch control.

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Pitch bend up: C4 to C5
c4 . & D(KCI, 0)
; [pitch bend commands would go here]
c5 .

r4

; Pitch bend down: C5 to C4
c5 . & D(KCI, 127)
c4 .

r4

; Rapid pitch sweep: C3 → C4 → C5 → C6
c3 .
c4 .
c5 .
c6 .

r4

; Wide interval jump
c4 .

r8
g4 .

r8

c4 .

r4

; Hold for settling
r2

#END
